---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
// Intro paragraph, status banner, why-cards, pilot section, and the roadmap all
// derive from the repo-root README at build time (between marker comments) — see
// lib/readme.ts. Experiment cards derive from ../experiments/*.md — see
// lib/experiments.ts.
import { readmeSection, readmeRoadmap, readmeWhy } from '../lib/readme';
import { getExperiments } from '../lib/experiments';

const github = 'https://github.com/tokedo/KamiBench';

// Copy on this page derives from README.md and paper/paper.md — reuse, condense,
// lightly rephrase; never escalate claims.

const ideaHtml = readmeSection('IDEA');
const statusHtml = readmeSection('STATUS', { inline: true });
const pilotHtml = readmeSection('PILOT');
const why = readmeWhy();
const roadmap = readmeRoadmap();
const experiments = getExperiments();

// The §3.1 today-vs-trajectory table from paper/paper.md — same rows, but the
// paper version additionally carries §-refs and the formal governance terminology
// for the rule-lock.
const propertyTable = [
  {
    property: 'On-chain state; complete readable history',
    today: 'Yes',
    trajectory: '—',
  },
  {
    property: 'Permissionless entry',
    today: 'Yes',
    trajectory: '—',
  },
  {
    property: 'Tamper-evident rule changes',
    today: 'Yes — every change is a public transaction',
    trajectory: '—',
  },
  {
    property: 'Persistence independent of any host’s funding',
    today: 'Partial — no central game server; state and rules live on-chain. Trust shifts to the chain that runs them',
    trajectory: 'Full once control is given up; possible migration to Ethereum',
  },
  {
    property: 'Rules permanently locked',
    today: 'No — the builders can still upgrade the contracts',
    trajectory: 'Handover to decentralized governance, then control given up entirely (years out)',
  },
];
---

<Base
  title="KamiBench — an agent benchmark in a persistent world that no one operates"
  description="A research program: long-horizon agent evaluation in a persistent world that no one operates."
  path="/"
>
  <header class="hero container">
    <h1>KamiBench</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      A research program: long-horizon agent evaluation in a persistent world that no
      one operates
    </p>
    <div class="btn-row">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/experiments">Experiments</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/paper">Paper</a>
      <a class="btn" href={github}>GitHub</a>
      <a class="btn" href="https://docs.asphodel.io/kamigotchi">Kamigotchi</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="container">
    <aside class="status-banner" role="note">
      <strong>Open research in progress</strong>
      <Fragment set:html={statusHtml} />
    </aside>
  </div>

  <section class="section container" aria-labelledby="idea">
    <h2 id="idea">The idea</h2>
    <div class="section-lead">
      <Fragment set:html={ideaHtml} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section container" aria-labelledby="why">
    <h2 id="why">Why a chain — and why this world</h2>
    <div class="section-lead">
      <Fragment set:html={why.leadHtml} />
    </div>
    <ul class="cards">
      {
        why.cards.map((card) => (
          <li class="card">
            <h3>{card.title}</h3>
            <p set:html={card.html} />
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ul>
    <p class="read-more">
      The paper develops this argument in full — the formalization, Kamigotchi as the
      best-fit instance available today, and the associated threats to validity.
      <a href="/paper">Read the paper →</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section container" aria-labelledby="today-vs-trajectory">
    <h2 id="today-vs-trajectory">Today vs. trajectory</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      Host-independence is a spectrum. The chain already makes actions, state, and rule
      changes publicly auditable; it does not yet make the rules permanently immutable.
      The table separates what holds today from what depends on future governance.
    </p>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Property</th>
            <th scope="col">Holds today</th>
            <th scope="col">Trajectory / mechanism</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {
            propertyTable.map((row) => (
              <tr>
                <td>{row.property}</td>
                <td>{row.today}</td>
                <td>{row.trajectory}</td>
              </tr>
            ))
          }
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="table-note">
      The honest present-tense claim is <strong>tamper-evident, not tamper-proof</strong>:
      silent patching is architecturally impossible because a rule change is itself a
      public, permanent transaction — the change history becomes part of the evaluation
      record. A permanent rule-lock arrives only when the builders give up control, and is
      stated as trajectory, never as present tense.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section container" aria-labelledby="experiments">
    <h2 id="experiments">Experiments</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      The registry of controlled experiments. Each design is published and
      git-timestamped before the run; results are appended without revising the
      registered protocol. Any amendment is explicit, dated, and preserves the
      original wording.
    </p>
    <ul class="cards exp-list">
      {
        experiments.map((exp) => (
          <li class="card exp-card">
            <p class="label">Experiment {exp.number}</p>
            <h3>
              <a href={`/experiments/${exp.slug}`}>{exp.title}</a>
            </h3>
            <p>{exp.oneliner}</p>
            <p class="exp-status">
              <span
                class={`chip ${exp.statusKind === 'complete' ? 'chip-ok' : 'chip-pending'}`}
              >
                {exp.statusLabel}
              </span>
              <span class="exp-status-note">{exp.status}</span>
            </p>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ul>
    <p class="read-more"><a href="/experiments">All experiments →</a></p>
  </section>

  <section class="section container" aria-labelledby="feasibility">
    <h2 id="feasibility">Feasibility pilot</h2>
    <div class="section-lead">
      <Fragment set:html={pilotHtml} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section container" aria-labelledby="roadmap">
    <h2 id="roadmap">Status &amp; roadmap</h2>
    <ul class="roadmap">
      {
        roadmap.map((item) => (
          <li>
            <span class={`chip ${item.done ? 'chip-ok' : 'chip-pending'}`}>
              {item.done ? 'Done' : 'Pending'}
            </span>
            <span set:html={item.html} />
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ul>
  </section>

</Base>
